## Overview

This document defines the standards for building and maintaining the **OffRoad Chabot** AI agent. The agent is a single-agent system built with **LangChain.js** and **TypeScript**, powered by **mistral-medium-latest**, using **Firebase Firestore** as the conversation memory store and **Tavily Search API** plus vehicle lookup as tools.

The agent's primary responsibilities are:
- Recognize returning users and load their profile from Firestore (`clients` collection)
- Know which 4x4 vehicle the user owns (make, model, year) and tailor advice accordingly
- Provide personalized off-road tips, maintenance guidance, trail recommendations, and gear suggestions
- Persist each conversation turn to Firestore (`conversations` collection)

