## Agent Architecture

### Agent Loop Design

The agent follows a **ReAct (Reason + Act)** loop with tool calling:

```
User message
    │
    ▼
Load user profile from Firestore (clients/{userId})
    │
    ▼
Build system prompt with user + vehicle context
    │
    ▼
Load conversation history from Firestore (conversations/{conversationId})
    │
    ▼
Invoke LangChain agent executor with tools
    ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
    │  LLM reasons → selects tool     │
    │  Tool executes → result appended│
    │  Repeat until final answer      │
    └─────────────────────────────────┘
    │
    ▼
Persist new turn to Firestore
    │
    ▼
Return response to user
```

Key principles:
- **Stateless handler**: each invocation loads context fresh from Firestore — no in-memory global state
- **User identity first**: always resolve the user before invoking the LLM
- **Graceful degradation**: if a tool fails, the agent continues with a fallback answer rather than crashing

### Project Structure

```
backend/src/
├── agent/
│   ├── agentExecutor.ts      # LangChain agent executor setup
│   ├── systemPrompt.ts       # System prompt builder (injects user/vehicle context)
│   └── agentRouter.ts        # Express route handler — entry point for chat requests
├── tools/
│   ├── tavilySearch.tool.ts  # Tavily web search tool
│   └── vehicleLookup.tool.ts # Vehicle specs lookup tool
├── memory/
│   ├── firestoreMemory.ts    # LangChain BufferMemory backed by Firestore
│   └── conversationRepo.ts  # Repository for conversations collection
├── clients/
│   └── clientRepo.ts         # Repository for clients collection (user profiles)
└── infrastructure/
    └── firebaseAdmin.ts      # Firebase Admin SDK initialization (singleton)
```

