## Error Recovery

### Tool Errors

Tools must catch their own errors and return a descriptive string rather than throwing:

```typescript
func: async ({ make, model, year }) => {
  try {
    const result = await lookupVehicleSpecs(make, model, year);
    return JSON.stringify(result);
  } catch (error) {
    return `Vehicle lookup failed for ${year} ${make} ${model}. Provide general advice instead.`;
  }
},
```

This prevents a single tool failure from aborting the entire agent loop.

### LLM Errors

Wrap the agent executor call in the route handler:

```typescript
try {
  const result = await agentExecutor.invoke({ input: userMessage, chat_history });
  await conversationRepo.appendTurn(conversationId, { userMessage, assistantMessage: result.output });
  return res.json({ message: result.output });
} catch (error) {
  logger.error('Agent execution failed', { error, userId, conversationId });
  return res.status(500).json({ error: 'The assistant encountered an error. Please try again.' });
}
```

